content: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?> <jnlp spec="1.5" codebase="http://jmars.mars.asu.edu/" href="http://jmars.mars.asu.edu/static/ucl-may2010.jnlp">  <information>   <title>JMARS for Earth - University College London, May 2010</title>   <vendor>Mars Space Flight Facility, Arizona State University</vendor>   <homepage href="http://jmars.mars.asu.edu"/>   <description>A Java based Geographic Information System</description>   <description kind="short">    JMARS is a Java based geographical information syatem.    It provides easy access to many different data sets    allowing the user to combine these into a single image.   </description>   <icon href="http://jmars.mars.asu.edu/images/JmarIcon64.jpg" width="64" height="64"/>   <icon kind="splash" href="http://jmars.mars.asu.edu/headerimg.gif" width="400" height="43"/>  <!-- TODO: not right now, as the handler will clash with other installs of jmars   <association mime-type="application/jmars-restart-file" extensions="jmars"/>  -->   <shortcut online="true">    <desktop/>    <menu submenu="JMARS for Earth - UCL May 2010"/>   </shortcut>   <related-content href="http://jmars.mars.asu.edu">    <title>JMARS Home</title>    <icon href="http://themis.asu.edu/images/homepage/asu_logo"/>   </related-content>  </information>  <security>   <all-permissions/>  </security>  <resources>   <j2se version="1.6+" initial-heap-size="128m" max-heap-size="1024m" java-vm-args=""/>   <jar href="http://jmars.mars.asu.edu/static/downloads/jmars-public-earth.jar"/>   <extention name="java3d" version="1.4" href="http://download.java.net/media/java3d/webstart/release/java3d-1.4-latest.jnlp"/>   <!-- custom code and properties to tell jmars about that code -->   <jar href="http://jmars.mars.asu.edu/static/uclshapes.jar"/>   <property name="jmars.shape.featurefactory.ucl_tracts" value="edu.asu.jmars.layer.util.features.FeatureProviderTracts" />   <property name="jmars.shape.featurefactory.ucl_markets" value="edu.asu.jmars.layer.util.features.FeatureProviderMarkets" />   <property name="jmars.shape.featurefactory.ucl_gardens" value="edu.asu.jmars.layer.util.features.FeatureProviderGardens" />   <property name="jmars.map.map_server.ucl_may2010.title" value="ucl_may2010" />   <property name="jmars.map.map_server.ucl_may2010.custom" value="false" />   <property name="jmars.map.map_server.ucl_may2010.timeout" value="10000" />   <property name="jmars.map.map_server.ucl_may2010.maxRequests" value="5" />   <property name="jmars.map.map_server.ucl_may2010.url" value="http://jmars.mars.asu.edu/static/ucl_may2010.xml" />   <!--   -->  </resources>  <application-desc main-class="edu.asu.jmars.Main">   <!-- custom session file that starts up ucl-may2010 users right the right settings -->   <argument>http://jmars.mars.asu.edu/static/ucl-startup.jmars</argument>  </application-desc> </jnlp>
